row-116.desc3: The type of document used for identifying the driver, expressed in text.

row-129.desc3: The main address line in a postal address usually the street name and number.

row-130.desc3: An additional address line in a postal address that can be used to give further details supplementing the main line. Common use are secondary house number in a complex or in a building.

row-131.desc3: The common name of the city where the postal address is. The name is written in full rather than as a code.

row-132.desc3: The identifier for an addressable group of properties according to the relevant national postal service, such as a ZIP code or Post Code.

row-133.desc3: For specifying a region, county, state, province etc. within a country by using text.

row-135.desc3: The country where the address is. The country should always be given by using ISO code 3166 alpha 2
